result.execSummary:
The defendant Shawne A Crary was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Shawne A Crary is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Shawne A Crary was found guilty of Burglary-Building or Dwelling, a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

timeConds.notes:
With huber. Stayed after 5 mo to Taycheedah for ATR, remaining months stayed. If successful in treatment, remainder of jail permanently stayed.
7/30/14: Crt orders JOC be amended to indicate that the Def shall serve 9 mo jail time as a condition of her probation, that the def will serve her conditional jail sentence until she is transferred to or placed at Taycheedah as part of an ATR for participation in the intensive AODA program, that the remainder of her sentence is stayed upon transfer to or placement at Taycheedah, and that upon successful completion of AODA program at Taycheedah, the remainder of the conditional jail sentence shall be permanently stayed.
